    <bug_when>2008-01-08 11:43:32 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>We should polish the API profile creation wizard. Perhaps it would be simpler for users to create profiles if we separate &quot;how&quot; to create the profile into a different page.

For example, currently the wizard has a drop-down/text box to specify the location of the bundles to place into the profile. If we put this on a first page we could support differnt creation methods (I can see that this may be different when targeting a p2 install). As well, this may allow us to infer the execution environment for the profile, rather than making the user select one.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
